column12:
I really wish parental leave would be lengthened. I also wish universal health care would be put in place to reduce reliance on a specific job for healthcare coverage and to make it less complicated. It is so complex and time-consuming to find a doctor, share health records, and get specialty care. I also wish the standard work week would be reduced to shift the balance of time slightly more towards family and personal time, because when you factor in commuting, the overwhelming majority of our time when my kids are at their youngest and neediest age is spent at a job.
We must find a way to provide public daycares and make daycare more affordable, and we must mandate public preschool in the national education system.
